Political Capital: Hungarian Guard Increases State Risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysing Division) of Political Capital, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, founded in August, with the support of the "Motion for Better Hungary", raised the risk of Hungary and the region in several respects.
The Institute's Risk Warning Report states, among other things, that, in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is the "increasing of the already existing ethnic tensions between the Zigeuner and the Non-Zigean population in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic conflicts in the short term".
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at provocating such a conflict, according to the Research Institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure by the political leaders: "Persons of public life have left the discussion of the Roma issue to representatives of radical political groups who have now built their political strategy on the Roma-Hungarian contrast".
It is assumed that this would exacerbate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, promote extremities, and increase the likelihood of violent conflicts.
The Research Institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard, not least thanks to the enormous attention of the domestic and foreign media, "the image of Hungary abroad would have greatly damaged, particularly in terms of confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
We remember: Since autumn 2006, the reorganization of radical and extreme right groups in Hungary has been continuing to rise, so since summer 2007, several organisations called themselves "national self-defense associations" have been established.
"These groups are common to define themselves as a civil organization, while they openly plead to prepare their members for - sometimes armed - defence tasks (civil protection, defence, order-keeping), calling for the inappropriateness of the police, the army or the state itself," it said.
And further: All this is done in accordance with that method, which attempts to shape various political aspirations based on the political and political democracy of the population as a bourgeois initiative.
So the emphasis on the civil character and the form of association are not just the circumvention of legal barriers that could arise in the course of the registration in court - it is at the same time a political strategy.
As the analysis shows, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are also a risk-enhancing factor for relations with neighbouring countries.
"In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been quoted as a potential source of danger in several neighbouring countries, as some ultranationalist politicians in certain neighbouring countries see in the creation of the Hungarian Guard the confirmation of its own anti-Hungarian policy.
All this has an impact on the political stability of the region" - it said.
From the point of view of the Research Institute, the establishment of the Hungarian Guard is not a single phenomenon in Central-Eastern Europe, so the political risk for the entire region has grown.
