For example, the alleged homosexuality or the mental disability of some deportation victims.
The lists of prisoners of the concentration camps or the arrest orders issued by the Gestapo had been collected after the war for a practical reason: to find civilians who had been deported or subjected to forced labour, and possibly to provide them with evidence of their arrest, so as to give them the way to their compensation.
