What insurance is best for me?
The motor vehicle insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, such as age, gender, date of issue of the driving licence, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
To own a car is only the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the appropriate KFZ insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we have to do here.
Auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance undertaking.
This agreement shall be concluded in writing by means of an insurance contract which establishes that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and, in return, is obliged to submit the corresponding amount of the disbursement in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that consists of several factors, including age, gender, date of issue of the driving licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to statistics, so that higher contributions are also payable in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women need to pay less contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons as they tend to be less accidental than those alone, according to statistical values, and therefore to the firm's conviction.
The benefit given to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In the setting of the premium, insurance must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
We now listen to the main points that should be considered when choosing an insurance in order not only to make a performance-oriented, but also to make a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing cheap insurance, such as low driving practices and the young driver's license.
Even if it is best for an ideal insurance protection to complete a full cash insurance, there are still more affordable alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full-casco with self-sufficiency, so that the benefits of a full-cass insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay a part of the amount incurred by the damage itself.
The amount will be fixed prior to the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher than the amount to be paid , explains Luis Noguera, the main representative of Spain at First Europe, an intermediary for online insurance.
Another option is the extended insurance, which assures customers against external damage to accidents, but not against damage caused by their own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hand to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in the tariffs referred to.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it can be able to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Therefore, it is most appropriate to choose a full cash insurance with self-sufficiency.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish director of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been lost.
However, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to make full cash insurance; of course only if it allows the financial situation of the person concerned.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and consequently their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, full cash insurance with equity (for a sum of EUR 300) would be the best option. In the case of a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which is not used until the third year of the vehicle.
They are generally more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment, says Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is possible to conclude a full cash insurance with self-sufficiency (for a amount of 150 euros) or an extended insurance that only uses a sufficient amount of credit.
Finally, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible damage to the accident, but also because it bears high costs that require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
